begin_memory_text: We began by introducing ourselves and went into how our days have been. It was a comfortable start to the conversation
middle_memory_text: We were speaking about life things such as work, family, home, and just life. We spoke about our perspective areas of living. It worked well because we are close in age.
end_memory_text: We spoke about influencing those around us. He is a teacher and it was truly a pleasure to get to speak with him and get some insight into what teaching is like nowadays
rest_of_day_open: Right now, I am babysitting and, as much as I love children, they are so very exhausting and make me feel much more than my age. I foresee a lot of resting in my future week because I have to recoup from the joys of kids. They are little bundles of energy and I am distinctly not.
critical_positive: We could relate rather well to each other due to there being a very similar age there. I could relate to him much more than many because I do not have too much access to people around my own age. When I do happen to be around people my age, I find that it is much easier for me to relate to them. But that is rare.
critical_negative: It was mostly my lack of energy. I wasn't having the most coherent conversation because I have had a headache all day and I am exhausted. I felt slow compared to my chat partner because my brain is like molasses. I did not bring my A game, sadly. I wish my youngest had taken a nap.

begin_memory_text: At the beginning we talked about hair and about being tired. We then talked about teaching and virtual school. We talked about how difficult it was to teach virtually and how there were many trade offs.
middle_memory_text: In the middle we talked about raising kids and how challenging it was for us. She talked about having kids in three different phases of her life. We talked about how raising kids has changed things and how it is different today.
end_memory_text: At the end we talked about how teaching is life changing and how Texas is different from Wisconsin. We talked about the seasons, and how it changes in each state. We ended the conversation each saying that we really enjoyed the time and wished it was long.
rest_of_day_open: I hope it will go well. In the COVID-19 world, each day has its ups and its challenges. There are some big things on the horizon and I just home they will go well. The week has been challenging, but there have also been a couple of really great things that have happened. No matter what, I will not give up.
critical_positive: We were similar in age and had a similar worldview. Since we were both parents, we could relate to the stress of the current situation. We both cared what the other person said and made sure to listen to each other. I think it also helped that we were both very positive and kept the conversation light and fun.
critical_negative: I don't think there was a part that didn't work. The conversation was free flowing and time went by really fast. We did not talk politics or religion, so there was no instance of disagreement. We each valued what the other person was saying and made sure that the other person could be heard. It was very enjoyable.
